    @FunctionalInterface
public interface ToBooleanFunction0
extends ToBooleanFunctionN, UnboxedResult<Function0<java.lang.Boolean>>, Variant<java.util.function.BooleanSupplier>
    Represents a function that accepts no arguments and produces a boolean-valued result. This is the zero-arity specialization of ToBooleanFunctionN. This is the boolean-producing primitive specialization of Function0.

    This is a functional interface whose functional method is applyAsBoolean().
